results.name: Number of orderless tree-factorizations of n.
comment: A factorization of n is a finite multiset of positive integers greater than 1 with product n. An orderless tree-factorization of n is either (case 1) the number n itself or (case 2) a finite multiset of two or more orderless tree-factorizations, one of each factor in a factorization of n.
a(n) depends only on the prime signature of n. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 18 2018
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..16384
Michael De Vlieger, Records and indices of records.
formula: a(p^n) = A141268(n) for prime p. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 18 2018
program: (PARI) seq(n)={my(v=vector(n), w=vector(n)); w[1]=v[1]=1; for(k=2, n, w[k]=v[k]+1; forstep(j=n\k*k, k, -k, my(i=j, e=0); while(i%k==0, i/=k; e++; v[j] += binomial(e+w[k]-1, e)*v[i]))); w} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 18 2018
